[{"slug":"dr-khan","name":"Dr. Hamza Khan","title":"Clinical Professor, Ophthalmologist","role":"Founder & Lead Ophthalmologist","image":"/img/hamza khan.avif","credentials":["MD Western '91","MPH Harvard '93","Ophthalmology Toronto '96","Cornea Fellowship Tulane '97"],"affiliations":["Clinical Professor, University of British Columbia, Department of Ophthalmology and Visual Sciences","Medical Staff, Island Health","Senior Achievement Award, American Academy of Ophthalmology","Faculty Advisor in Quality Improvement","Surgical Quality Council Lead Physician"],"bio":["Dr. Hamza Khan is committed to patient safety and to providing high quality ophthalmology care. Having founded Victoria Eyecare as a solo practice in 2002, he is gratified to see the fine team of doctors and staff that continue to provide patient centred care. He currently coaches other physicians on Healthcare Quality Improvement skills as well as patient communication.","Dr. Khan has delivered over one hundred invited lectures at national and international conferences. He has also authored numerous peer-reviewed articles, chapters in textbooks on cataract surgery, and is the coeditor of the textbook, Surgical Correction of Astigmatism (Springer; 2019). He is a current Faculty Advisor in Quality Improvement and Surgical Quality Council Lead Physician.","At Harvard University, Dr. Khan focused his studies on Health Care Quality Improvement. In addition to residency in Ophthalmology (Toronto), he specialized in Cornea and Refractive surgery through a fellowship at Tulane University in New Orleans.","He gains great enjoyment from hiking (or running) the many trails in and around Victoria."],"specializations":["Cataract Surgery","Cornea","Refractive Surgery","Healthcare Quality Improvement"]},{"slug":"dr-duimering","name":"Dr. Adrienne Duimering","title":"Ophthalmologist","role":"Ophthalmologist","image":"/img/ADuimering.avif","credentials":["MD UBC '17","Ophthalmology Queens '22"],"affiliations":[],"bio":["Dr. Adrienne Duimering provides considerate patient care, ensuring that patients thoroughly understand their treatment. From Victoria, she is happy to have the opportunity to contribute to health care in the community where she was raised.","She completed a B.Sc. at the University of Victoria. During her undergraduate years, Dr. Duimering explored her passion for teaching and science outreach working in rural communities across Vancouver Island. She continued her studies on the Island, receiving her M.D. at the University of British Columbia Island Medical Program.","At Queens University, Dr. Duimering completed her residency. During residency, her research focused on applying machine learning and motion analysis to surgery to create a feedback platform for learners.","Dr. Duimering appreciates being back home on the west coast and is looking forward to providing eye care to her community."],"specializations":["General Ophthalmology","Surgical Innovation","Community Eye Care"]}]